[normal]Written evidence from Compass Disability Services (PIC 0010)
[normal]Compass Disability Service
[normal]s
[normal] 
[normal]is
[normal] a user led organisation based in Somerset but also operating in different parts of the country providing
[normal] services which promote independent living.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We carry out consultation work with disabled people and carers in Somerset through our Network project.  We work with local authorities to consult on issues that disabled people may be interested in having their say on.  We also carry out Disability Forums and Discussion Groups inviting speakers to engage with disabled people and carers and give them a chance to have their voice heard.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We have been asked to carry out consultation work for Somerset County Council on topics such as the ‘Long Term Transport Strategy for Somerset’ in 2010 and the ‘Bus Subsidies Reduction Consultation’ in January 2012.  In addition to this, issues regarding transport ha
[normal]ve
[normal] been raised by our members at our disability groups and forums.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]This information is summarised below;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Public Transport[bold]              
[normal]Even in more urban areas such as Taunton, disabled people who 
[normal]              
[normal]are wheelchair users have to wait sometimes close to 2 hours for a 
[normal]              
[normal]public transport bus with a ramp which is suitable for them.  
[normal]There 
[normal]              
[normal]is only 
[normal]1disabled space for a wheelchair on public transport and 
[normal]              
[normal]there are inconsistencies in staff attitudes in assisting people to 
[normal]              
[normal]access buses. 
[normal]Bus drivers can ask for other passengers to 
[normal]              
[normal]collapse buggies to a
[normal]ssist access but cannot insist, 
[normal]this relies on 
[normal]              
[normal]members of the public being 
[normal]              
[normal]helpful.
[normal]              
[normal]There are l
[normal]imitation
[normal]s 
[normal]of access
[normal] with
[normal] smaller buses in rural area
[normal]s.
